# Frontend Project Structure Guide

## Project Overview
This is a modern Next.js 15 frontend application using React 19, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, and shadcn/ui components for the FRAI AI Boilerplate.

## Key Entry Points
- Main application: [src/app/page.tsx](mdc:frontend/src/app/page.tsx)
- Root layout: [src/app/layout.tsx](mdc:frontend/src/app/layout.tsx)
- App configuration: [next.config.js](mdc:frontend/next.config.js)
- TypeScript config: [tsconfig.json](mdc:frontend/tsconfig.json)

## Core Architecture
- **Next.js 15**: App Router with React Server Components
- **React 19**: Latest React with concurrent features
- **TypeScript 5.8**: Strict type checking and modern features
- **Tailwind CSS 4.0**: Utility-first CSS framework
- **shadcn/ui**: Radix UI-based component library
- **Zod**: Runtime type validation

## Directory Structure
- `src/app/`: Next.js App Router pages and layouts
  - `api/`: API routes for backend communication
  - `layout.tsx`: Root layout component
  - `page.tsx`: Home page component
- `src/components/`: Reusable React components
  - `ui/`: shadcn/ui components
  - `navigation.tsx`: Navigation component
- `src/lib/`: Utility functions and configurations
- `src/styles/`: Global CSS and Tailwind configuration
- `public/`: Static assets

## Development Commands
- `pnpm dev`: Start development server with Turbo
- `pnpm build`: Build for production
- `pnpm lint`: Run ESLint
- `pnpm lint:fix`: Fix ESLint issues
- `pnpm format:write`: Format code with Prettier
- `pnpm typecheck`: Run TypeScript type checking

